<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1870-08-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1870-08-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="6" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d6">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">No. 6.</note>
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. J. R. Jones</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Fish</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 54.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United
                                        States,</hi><hi rend="italic"> Brussels,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1870-08-11"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 11, 1870</date>. (Received August 24,
                                1870.)</dateline></opener>
                        <p rend="center">* * * * * * * * *</p>
                        <p>Mr. Motley telegraphed me yesterday, as follows:</p>
                        <p>Please inform Generals Sheridan and Forsythe that Count Bismarck informs
                            Count Bernstorff that they will be welcome at headquarters.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>J. R. JONES.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>